        procedure: ['Bring a large pot of water to a rolling boil. Add a generous amount of salt, then add the spaghetti and cook until al dente (firm to the bite).','Just before draining, reserve about 1 cup of the starchy pasta water. This is the key to the sauce!','While the pasta cooks, heat the olive oil in a large skillet or pan over medium-low heat. Add thinly sliced garlic and cook slowly, stirring often, until it turns a light golden color. Be careful not to burn it, or it will become bitter.','Add the red pepper flakes to the oil and cook for another 30 seconds until fragrant.','Drain the cooked pasta and immediately add it to the skillet with the garlic oil. Toss everything together vigorously for about a minute to coat the pasta.','Add a few tablespoons of the reserved pasta water to the skillet and continue to toss. The starchy water will emulsify with the oil to create a light, creamy sauce.','Turn off the heat, add the chopped fresh parsley, and give it one final toss. Serve immediately.']
