        procedure: ['Rinse the sushi rice under cold water until the water runs clear. Cook the rice with 1.25 cups of water according to package directions. Once cooked, gently fold in the seasoned rice vinegar while the rice is still hot. Let it cool to room temperature.','Place a sheet of nori, shiny side down, on a bamboo rolling mat.','Keep a small bowl of water handy to wet your fingers, which prevents the rice from sticking to them.','Spread about half of the cooled sushi rice over the nori in a thin, even layer, leaving a 1-inch border at the top edge.','Arrange sticks of crab, slices of avocado, and strips of cucumber in a horizontal line about 1 inch from the bottom edge of the nori.','From the bottom, begin rolling the sushi tightly using the bamboo mat to apply firm, even pressure. When you reach the end, dab a little water on the nori border to help seal the roll.','Use a very sharp and wet knife to slice the roll into 8 equal pieces. Repeat the process to make a second roll.']
