        procedure: ['First, prepare the filling. Heat 1 tbsp of oil in a pan over medium heat. Add the cumin seeds and let them splutter.','Add the ginger-garlic paste and sauté for one minute until fragrant.','Add the mashed potatoes, boiled green peas, garam masala, and salt. Mix everything thoroughly and cook for 5-7 minutes. Set the filling aside to cool completely.','Prepare the samosa pockets. If using dough, roll it into a thin oval and cut it in half. Form a cone shape from one semi-circle, moistening the straight edge with water to seal it.','Stuff the cone with the cooled potato filling. Do not overfill. Apply a little water to the top edge and pinch it tightly to seal the samosa completely.','Heat oil in a deep pan or kadai over medium-low heat. The oil should not be too hot. Gently slide a few samosas into the oil and fry them on low heat, turning occasionally, for 10-15 minutes until they are golden brown and crispy all over.']
